'''伏尔泰的朋友们'''是[[伊夫林·比阿特丽斯·霍尔|伊夫林·比阿特丽斯·霍尔]]以笔名S.G. Tallentyre写作的一部作品，出版于1906年，<ref Name="Tallentyre">{{cite book  | last =S. G. Tallentyre  | first =  | authorlink =S.G. Tallentyre  | title =伏尔泰的朋友们  | publisher =Richard West  | date =1906  | location =  | pages =  | url =http://books.google.com/books?id=jOq2AAAACAAJ&dq=%22The+Friends+of+Voltaire%22+Tallentyre&source=gbs_book_other_versions_r&cad=1_0  | doi =  | id =ISBN 0827423772  | access-date =2008-08-06  | archive-date =2014-01-11  | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140111221740/http://books.google.com/books?id=jOq2AAAACAAJ&dq=%22The+Friends+of+Voltaire%22+Tallentyre&source=gbs_book_other_versions_r&cad=1_0  | dead-url =no  }}</ref> 1907年，由Putnam's Sons以其真名在[[英国|英国]]出版。<ref Name="Hall">{{cite book  | last =霍尔  | first =伊夫林·比阿特丽斯  | authorlink =伊夫林·比阿特丽斯·霍尔  | coauthors =  | title =伏尔泰的朋友们 | publisher =Putnam's Sons | date =1907  | location =  | pages =  | url =http://books.google.com/books?id=qQf2GAAACAAJ&dq=%22The+Friends+of+Voltaire%22  | doi =  | id =  }}</ref>这本关于[[伏尔泰|伏尔泰]]的经典著作仍然在近100年后的2003年继续发行。<ref Name="Tallentyre_2003">{{cite book  | last =S. G. Tallentyre  | first =  | authorlink =S.G. Tallentyre  | coauthors =  | title =伏尔泰的朋友们  | publisher =University Press of the Pacific  | date =2003  | location =  | pages =第332页  | url =http://books.google.com/books?id=0OEGAAAACAAJ&dq=%22The+Friends+of+Voltaire%22+Tallentyre  | doi =  | id =ISBN 1410210200  | access-date =2008-08-06  | archive-date =2014-01-11  | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140111221804/http://books.google.com/books?id=0OEGAAAACAAJ&dq=%22The+Friends+of+Voltaire%22+Tallentyre  | dead-url =no  }}</ref> 霍尔在本书中以“我不同意你的意見，但我以死捍衛你說話的權利”来阐释伏尔泰的思想，这句话成为了捍卫[[言论自由|言论自由]]的名言，但常被误认为是伏尔泰本人所述。<ref>{{cite book |last=Boller, Jr. |first=Paul F. |authorlink= |author2=George, John |title=They Never Said It: A Book of Fake Quotes, Misquotes, and Misleading Attributions |url=https://archive.org/details/theyneversaiditb00boll |year=1989 |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=New York |isbn=0-19-505541-1|pages=[https://archive.org/details/theyneversaiditb00boll/page/124 124]-126 }}</ref>

伏尔泰广泛传颂的名言“我并不同意你的观点，但是我誓死捍卫你说话的权利。({{lang-fr|Je ne suis pas d'accord avec ce que vous dites, mais je me battrai jusqu'à la mort pour que vous ayez le droit de le dire.}}，{{lang-en|I disapprove of what you say, but I will defend to the death your right to say it.}})”即为本书为表达伏尔泰的观点所杜撰。作者霍尔以此句总结整理了伏尔泰反对君主专制制度，提倡自然神论，批判天主教会，主张言论自由的观点，伏尔泰本人并没有真正说过这句话。

这本书以趣闻轶事的传记方式记叙了10个生活非常接近的人的故事。这十个人处于同一时代，除了与伏尔泰的友谊外他们或多或少的彼此相互有着联系。这10个人中的每一个人都被赋予以下的几种明显的性格：D'Alembert是思考者、Diderot是谈论者、Galiani是智者、Vauvenargues是警句家、多尔巴赫是东道主、Grimm是记者、埃尔维修斯是反驳者、Turgot是政治家、Beaumarchais是剧作家以及Condorcet是贵族。<ref Name="Smith">{{cite book  | last =Josiay Renick Smith整理；Francis Fisher Browne编辑  | title =The Dial  | publisher =Jansen, McClurg  | date =1907  | location =密歇根大学原版  | pages =第58～60页  | url =http://books.google.com/books?id=vtI9AAAAMAAJ&pg=RA1-PA58&dq=%22The+Friends+of+Voltaire%22+Tallentyre#PRA1-PA59,M1  | doi =  | id =  | access-date =2008-08-06  | archive-date =2014-06-22  | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140622233917/http://books.google.com/books?id=vtI9AAAAMAAJ&pg=RA1-PA58&dq=%22The+Friends+of+Voltaire%22+Tallentyre#PRA1-PA59,M1  | dead-url =no  }}</ref>

